               <p>WILLIAM ISBESTER. I am a Thames Police constable. On the 13th of May, about five o'clock in the morning, I observed the prisoner and another on board a barge, which laid at <placeName id="t18190526-123-crimeloc679">Bell Wharf tier on the Middlesex side</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190526-123-crimeloc679" type="placeName" value="Bell Wharf tier on the Middlesex side"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190526-123-crimeloc679" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190526-123-off676 t18190526-123-crimeloc679"></join>; they took coals out in a basket, and put them into their boat - they then got into the boat. I pursued them to the next tier; they then jumped out of the boat, ran over the tier, and got on board one of the ships; I secured the prisoner without losing sight of him; I found about ten bushels of coals in the boat - the name of of the barge is Tommy. The prisoner offered me his watch to let him go.</p>
               <p>
            
